upon sight.

12:06.942 --> 12:09.309
I would not have streets swollen
with bodies errant rebels

12:09.377 --> 12:11.512
yet could secret
themselves among.

12:11.579 --> 12:14.547
Though deserving few shall
be granted consideration.

12:14.615 --> 12:16.583
<i>Dispatch your men</i>
<i>and see all upon this</i>

12:16.650 --> 12:17.817
brought to villa.

12:17.885 --> 12:18.985
Imperator.

12:19.053 --> 12:20.653
♪

12:23.424 --> 12:25.592
Ah, you return to form,
Caesar.

12:25.660 --> 12:27.327
<i>A most</i>
<i>welcomed sight.</i>

12:27.395 --> 12:29.296
<i>I was only just praising</i>
<i>him for his ability</i>

12:29.364 --> 12:32.599
to blend so effortlessly
with a pack of savage dogs.

12:32.667 --> 12:34.435
A thing
of ill consideration,

12:34.502 --> 12:37.638
had Crassus not plucked
scheme from fevered brain.

12:37.706 --> 12:40.107
<i>I am of regret to have</i>
<i>ever laid doubt upon it.</i>

12:40.175 --> 12:41.442
The Senate
will be most pleased

12:41.509 --> 12:44.111
to greet news of
Sinuessa en Valle's liberation.

12:44.178 --> 12:45.846
<i>Linger before</i>
<i>return to Rome,</i>

12:45.913 --> 12:47.881
see it celebrated
with Carnificina.

12:49.551 --> 12:50.484
Executions?

12:50.552 --> 12:52.052
As night
greets us.

12:52.120 --> 12:53.854
I've set aside
one of the finest villas

12:53.922 --> 12:55.889
for you to rest
and see yourself to bath,

12:55.957 --> 12:58.058
until such
a time.

12:58.126 --> 13:02.295
A gesture unexpected,
yet much appreciated.

13:02.363 --> 13:04.130
<i>Gratitude.</i>

13:10.366 --> 13:12.835
Preening little fuck.

13:12.902 --> 13:15.404
A sentiment shared.

13:15.471 --> 13:17.239
Yet he holds
the ear of the Senate,

13:17.306 --> 13:19.174
and I would see him
well satisfied

13:19.241 --> 13:21.209
to further bolster
tale of our victory

13:21.277 --> 13:24.812
carried back
to Rome.

13:24.879 --> 13:28.982
You speak again of victory
shrouded from discerning eye.

13:29.049 --> 13:30.383
Spartacus yet lives,

13:30.451 --> 13:34.254
with considerable force
aiding him upon Melia Ridge.

13:34.322 --> 13:36.189
There is no escape
from the ridge.

13:36.257 --> 13:37.891
It stands impassable.

13:37.959 --> 13:40.728
Words most likely
broken by the fool Glaber

13:40.796 --> 13:42.964
<i>when he had the rebel</i>
<i>trapped upon Vesuvius.</i>

13:43.031 --> 13:44.966
♪

13:47.035 --> 13:50.438
You believe
me the fool?

13:50.506 --> 13:53.975
I believe you a man
of infinite plots,

13:54.043 --> 13:57.446
<i>twisting upon themselves</i>
<i>to shame Gordian knot.</i>

13:57.513 --> 13:59.581
Praise well received.

13:59.649 --> 14:01.449
Now part mind from
troubled thoughts,

14:01.517 --> 14:03.051
<i>and allow</i>
<i>it returned.</i>

14:03.119 --> 14:06.254
The rebellion
has suffered fatal blow.

14:06.321 --> 14:10.058
At celebration I would
honor hand that struck it.

14:10.125 --> 14:11.993
Would that
the Thracian's head

14:12.061 --> 14:15.763
upon pike bore witness
to such laurels.

14:15.831 --> 14:17.531
<i>Hold fast</i>
<i>to patience,</i>

14:17.599 --> 14:19.200
a thing that has propelled
us to the ground

14:19.267 --> 14:20.668
we now stand upon.

14:20.735 --> 14:24.438
And in briefest passing
shall claim Spartacus

14:25.874 --> 14:29.143
and all those who yet follow
the doom of his shadow.

14:35.583 --> 14:36.984
<i>[ shattering ]</i>
<i>[ grunting ]</i>

14:43.129 --> 14:44.232
<i>No one's here.</i>

14:44.300 --> 14:47.138
<i>[ banging ]</i>
<i>[ footsteps ]</i>

14:47.206 --> 14:49.608
[ whispering ]
They take leave?

14:49.675 --> 14:51.376
<i>Not all.</i>

14:51.445 --> 14:55.848
Thousands more
swell in streets.

14:55.916 --> 14:58.685
<i>The ones above</i>
<i>spoke of victory,</i>

14:58.752 --> 15:02.155
great numbers
lost to us.

15:02.222 --> 15:05.224
Coupled with the curse that
Spartacus yet eludes them.

15:09.496 --> 15:12.298
He is a troublesome
man to kill.

15:12.366 --> 15:14.601
I have attempted
it myself upon occasion.

15:18.239 --> 15:20.374
The gods
favor him.

15:20.442 --> 15:22.278
And bless
us as well.

15:22.346 --> 15:23.482
They piss
upon us

15:23.549 --> 15:26.084
and you welcome
it as cooling rain.

15:26.152 --> 15:27.719
We are alive.

15:27.787 --> 15:30.288
Because they
yet guide your hand.

15:30.356 --> 15:32.825
One I have faith
will see us from darkest hour.

15:37.298 --> 15:38.865
Would that
I shared the same.

15:38.933 --> 15:40.933
♪

15:41.001 --> 15:43.736
You have done
this before.

15:43.804 --> 15:47.340
My Dominus inflicted many
wounds upon his slaves.

15:47.408 --> 15:50.209
I often tended
their injuries.

15:50.277 --> 15:55.515
Who tended yours?

15:55.582 --> 15:59.086
Diotimus showed a kindness.

15:59.153 --> 16:01.221
Did he now?

16:01.289 --> 16:02.923
He stood as a brother to me.

16:04.726 --> 16:07.194
Apologies.

16:07.262 --> 16:10.631
You struck down
the man that took his life.

16:10.699 --> 16:12.433
The man that took my own,

16:12.501 --> 16:15.903
a small piece at a time
over span of years.

16:20.609 --> 16:23.544
Would that it had
made difference.

16:23.612 --> 16:26.447
You have made
all in the world.

16:32.721 --> 16:34.455
[ thud ]

16:41.565 --> 16:43.399
[ whimpering ]

16:46.870 --> 16:49.204
Hold!

16:49.272 --> 16:51.841
See her hands freed of bond.

16:51.908 --> 16:53.576
This woman stands
no fucking slave.

16:58.115 --> 16:59.349
I know you.

16:59.417 --> 17:01.284
Do I not?

17:01.352 --> 17:02.752
You have laid eyes
upon distorted

17:02.820 --> 17:05.323
reflection of the man
before you.

17:05.390 --> 17:07.492
I was secreted among
the rebels,

17:07.560 --> 17:10.195
beard upon cheek
and lies upon tongue.

17:10.263 --> 17:12.866
You stood with
Crixus and his animals

17:12.934 --> 17:14.094
as they slaughtered
my people,

17:14.101 --> 17:15.367
bound in chains.

17:15.435 --> 17:17.203
A deed of much regret.

17:17.271 --> 17:19.071
Yet born of necessity.

17:19.138 --> 17:20.306
I could not risk

17:20.374 --> 17:23.376
discovery short of turning
the Cilicians to our cause.

17:25.747 --> 17:30.985
In war, one does what
one must to survive.

17:31.052 --> 17:33.688
A burden not unfamiliar.

17:35.524 --> 17:37.258
Crassus would have word.

17:37.326 --> 17:38.459
You are to
be fed proper meal

17:38.526 --> 17:39.960
and bathed in rosewater,

17:40.028 --> 17:43.527
in the villa you once
called home.

17:43.594 --> 17:45.195
Come.

17:58.835 --> 18:00.436
♪

18:14.119 --> 18:15.986
Apologies.

18:16.054 --> 18:17.888
I did not move
to frighten.

18:17.956 --> 18:20.391
Recent events set
nerves to edge.

18:23.662 --> 18:26.464
See grave
concern give way.

18:26.532 --> 18:28.066
The city is taken,

18:28.134 --> 18:30.168
and I stand unscathed.

18:30.236 --> 18:32.204
A great victory.

18:32.271 --> 18:34.239
One whose celebration,

18:34.307 --> 18:36.074
I would have
you share in.

18:39.312 --> 18:42.014
I am to stay here,
with you?

18:42.082 --> 18:44.016
Would you stand
pleased by it?

18:44.083 --> 18:45.984
Beyond the telling of words.
[ chuckles ]

18:48.855 --> 18:51.089
There is no
cause for tears

18:51.157 --> 18:52.557
on such a day.

18:52.625 --> 18:54.626
They are of joy,

18:54.694 --> 18:58.030
to find myself delivered
from followers' camp.

18:58.098 --> 19:00.433
Delivered?

19:00.501 --> 19:02.068
Has it grown
so unpleasant?

19:03.771 --> 19:06.806
Unbearably so...

19:06.874 --> 19:09.275
<i>The fault is mine.</i>

19:12.847 --> 19:15.482
I lay upon Kore
heavy burden,

19:15.550 --> 19:17.451
<i>of lending ear</i>
<i>to my grief</i>

19:17.519 --> 19:20.721
in the passing of Sabinus.

19:20.788 --> 19:23.223
And my hand in it.

19:23.290 --> 19:25.258
A man does
what is required,

19:25.326 --> 19:27.427
when fate calls upon him.

19:27.495 --> 19:30.664
As all soldiers must.

19:30.732 --> 19:32.433
Kore served greater comfort

19:32.500 --> 19:33.701
than you will ever know.

19:33.768 --> 19:36.804
Yet I fear my pain has,

19:36.872 --> 19:39.406
pressed hard against her.

19:39.474 --> 19:40.908
I pray you are
not too delicate

19:40.976 --> 19:43.777
to bear such weight.

19:43.845 --> 19:47.581
I stand no soldier
in this conflict.

19:47.649 --> 19:50.084
Yet I too shall
do what I must.

19:52.421 --> 19:55.389
I am forever grateful.

19:55.457 --> 19:57.758
See wine and food prepared.

19:57.826 --> 19:59.393
Yes, Dominus.

20:06.701 --> 20:09.769
This war has
forever changed her.

20:09.837 --> 20:13.540
She does not stand
alone is such regard.

20:13.607 --> 20:16.509
I am but hardened by it,

20:16.577 --> 20:20.247
and the lessons
it has taught.

20:20.315 --> 20:22.283
I had thought decimation

20:22.351 --> 20:26.287
in threat of pulling
you from reason.

20:26.355 --> 20:28.890
Yet you rise
like the phoenix,

20:28.958 --> 20:31.726
the fire of purpose
filling eye.

20:31.794 --> 20:34.595
And soon shall
take your place again

20:34.663 --> 20:36.664
<i>as my word and my will.</i>

20:36.732 --> 20:38.566
Soon?

20:38.634 --> 20:40.234
You did not summon
to reinstate

20:40.302 --> 20:41.735
me into the legion?

20:41.803 --> 20:42.763
I would have you present

20:42.804 --> 20:45.573
Carnificina for the men.

20:45.640 --> 20:46.574
It will elevate you

20:46.641 --> 20:47.742
in the eyes of the legion

20:47.809 --> 20:50.011
to be seen in such
giving spirit.

20:50.078 --> 20:51.779
<i>And ease the way</i>
<i>for you</i>

20:51.847 --> 20:53.381
to again assume command.

20:53.449 --> 20:55.250
A privilege then.

20:55.318 --> 20:57.185
And opportunity
to honor you

20:57.253 --> 20:58.419
<i>and your triumph.</i>

20:58.487 --> 21:01.056
You mistake intent.

21:01.123 --> 21:03.691
We shall honor
Caesar as the victor.

21:07.029 --> 21:09.264
There is no love
lost between us.

21:09.331 --> 21:11.799
Surely there must be more
fitting service that I might --

21:11.867 --> 21:15.802
A shrewd man turns rival
to valued ally.

21:15.870 --> 21:17.871
<i>Caesar is blessed</i>
<i>with</i> storied name,

21:17.939 --> 21:22.242
and shall one day
rise to shame the very sun.

21:22.310 --> 21:23.710
Make peace,

21:23.778 --> 21:26.046
and bask
in glorious light.

21:28.349 --> 21:33.653
He shall be awarded
all respect deserved.

21:33.721 --> 21:36.957
Many a boy may enter a war.

21:37.025 --> 21:38.659
Yet at it's end,

21:38.726 --> 21:42.668
only a man will emerge.

21:42.736 --> 21:46.209
It warms my heart
to see you become one.

21:46.277 --> 21:53.218
I am what you have made me.

21:53.285 --> 21:56.555
[ patting ]

21:56.623 --> 21:58.824
[ breathing heavy ]

22:02.262 --> 22:04.564
More soldiers return.

22:04.632 --> 22:07.267
<i>They pry wood and beams</i>
<i>searching for vermin.</i>

22:07.335 --> 22:08.668
<i>[ footsteps ]</i>

22:08.736 --> 22:10.804
If we stay,
will they not find us?

22:10.871 --> 22:13.272
They will.

22:13.340 --> 22:14.707
Is there nothing we can do?

22:16.677 --> 22:19.145
There is but one thing.

22:20.947 --> 22:21.881
Pray.

22:21.949 --> 22:37.130
[ grunting ]
[ wood cracking ]

22:51.511 --> 22:53.712
If any but my visage return,

22:53.780 --> 22:55.147
take your life.

22:55.215 --> 22:56.582
<i>It will be a kindness</i>
<i>in comparison</i>

22:56.649 --> 22:58.250
to what they
will do to you.

23:07.259 --> 23:09.059
[ footsteps ]

23:09.126 --> 23:10.459
[ grunting ]

23:10.526 --> 23:11.459
<i>Rebel!</i>

23:11.527 --> 23:12.460
<i>Here!</i>

23:12.527 --> 23:14.661
[ clanking ]

23:14.729 --> 23:18.964
<i>I got him!</i>
[ grunting ]

23:19.032 --> 23:24.236
[ clanging ]

23:24.304 --> 23:40.182
[ footsteps ]

23:41.885 --> 23:43.919
I begin to believe
in your gods.

23:43.987 --> 23:44.920
[ exhale ]

23:44.988 --> 23:53.327
Let us see how far
they will take us.

23:53.394 --> 23:55.162
Falernian.

23:55.229 --> 23:56.530
A taste I recall you favor.

23:56.597 --> 23:59.332
It is for your father.

23:59.399 --> 24:01.667
As are many things.

24:01.735 --> 24:04.703
The Imperator has much
pressing upon mind.

24:04.771 --> 24:05.871
<i>Laying more upon it</i>

24:05.938 --> 24:08.907
<i>would only serve to open</i>
<i>grievous</i> wound.

24:08.975 --> 24:10.975
Do all the years
I have cared for you

24:11.043 --> 24:12.344
stand for nothing?

24:14.814 --> 24:18.783
They have brought
me greatest comfort.

24:18.851 --> 24:20.284
It would sadden heart,

24:20.352 --> 24:22.386
to see you
turned from our house.

24:22.454 --> 24:25.422
Or set to
cruelest punishment...

24:25.490 --> 24:28.257
If he ever learned
how you willingly

24:28.325 --> 24:30.893
gave yourself to me
in attempt to ease my pain.

24:33.030 --> 24:35.564
If errant word
falls from mouth,

24:35.632 --> 24:38.134
only suffering
will follow them.

24:38.202 --> 24:40.570
At the hands
of the Imperator.

24:40.638 --> 24:44.808
Or my own.

24:44.875 --> 24:47.410
And I will not be
as gentle next time.

26:04.724 --> 26:07.192
You stand a vision.

26:07.259 --> 26:09.294
<i>One to rival my</i>
<i>own beloved wife.</i>

26:09.362 --> 26:12.164
<i>It is as a dream,</i>
<i>to be resurrected so.</i>

26:16.369 --> 26:18.103
Come.

26:18.171 --> 26:20.539
Crassus awaits your company.

26:34.453 --> 26:36.020
She has been prepared,

26:36.088 --> 26:37.122
as commanded.

26:37.189 --> 26:38.924
When last I laid eyes,

26:38.991 --> 26:41.259
you appeared
as defiled effigy,

26:41.327 --> 26:43.463
marred by
calamity of war.

26:43.530 --> 26:46.900
Now restored to graven
image of Venus herself.

26:46.968 --> 26:48.435
Gratitude.

26:48.503 --> 26:50.704
<i>For all that you have done.</i>

26:50.772 --> 26:52.439
I would take my leave,

26:52.507 --> 26:54.308
if I am
of no further use.

26:54.376 --> 26:57.044
Fall to your chambers
in advance of celebration.

26:57.112 --> 26:58.913
<i>You shall find</i>
<i>welcomed gifts,</i>

26:58.980 --> 27:00.348
most deserved.

27:03.018 --> 27:04.386
You hold celebration?

27:04.454 --> 27:06.154
Carnificina.

27:06.222 --> 27:09.192
In honor of our victory
against the rebel king.

27:09.260 --> 27:10.527
Apologies.

27:10.595 --> 27:12.864
I fear I am not yet
of strength --

27:12.931 --> 27:16.401
I did not imagine you would
be of attendance.

27:16.469 --> 27:19.238
It is a blessing you
yet draw breath.

27:19.306 --> 27:23.141
One bestowed by Spartacus
himself, was it not?

27:23.209 --> 27:25.077
As I have told you,

27:25.145 --> 27:27.180
I exchanged words with
the man only in hope

27:27.247 --> 27:29.315
of sparing what
remained of my people.

27:29.383 --> 27:31.785
Know that I find
no fault in it.

27:31.852 --> 27:33.386
The whole of Rome
echoes with

27:33.454 --> 27:36.823
inflated legend
of the Bringer of Rain.

27:36.890 --> 27:39.092
I would hear air filled
with truer tale,

27:39.159 --> 27:42.161
of Spartacus the man.

27:42.228 --> 27:46.131
I knew him only as captor.

27:46.199 --> 27:48.801
I do not move to trap you.

27:48.869 --> 27:52.171
I but crave honest appraisal
of worthy adversary.

27:52.239 --> 27:55.341
One I shall soon meet
upon field of battle.

27:57.244 --> 27:59.712
Spartacus seems...

28:03.484 --> 28:05.352
not the beast,

28:05.420 --> 28:08.588
one would form thought of.

28:08.656 --> 28:15.295
And in place of horns
and sharpened claw?

28:15.363 --> 28:17.462
A wounded heart.

28:17.530 --> 28:19.631
Yearning to
balance scale.

28:21.600 --> 28:23.368
I know of his wife,

28:23.436 --> 28:26.070
and his thirst
to avenge her death.

28:26.138 --> 28:28.607
No he is not consumed
by a thirst for blood.

28:28.674 --> 28:30.809
<i>Perhaps he stood</i>
<i>as such</i> <i>once,</i>

28:30.876 --> 28:33.845
<i>yet now...</i>

28:33.913 --> 28:37.315
he fights for what
he believes is just.

28:37.383 --> 28:40.251
There is no cause
more dangerous.

28:40.319 --> 28:42.587
He will not stop.

28:42.654 --> 28:43.621
I do not believe he could,

28:43.689 --> 28:45.790
even if he so wished it.

28:48.727 --> 28:51.462
Then he and I stand the same.

28:51.530 --> 28:54.198
Each believes
himself the hero,

28:54.266 --> 28:56.534
the other villain.

28:56.602 --> 29:00.037
It is for history
to decide who is mistaken.

29:00.105 --> 29:01.439
<i>Until such</i> <i>a day,</i>

29:01.507 --> 29:06.177
we shall play our parts
upon fortune's stage.

29:06.245 --> 29:07.478
As each of us must.

29:07.546 --> 29:09.046
[ foot steps approaching ]

29:16.955 --> 29:18.922
The city is yours,
mighty Crassus!

29:18.990 --> 29:21.024
<i>I would see to agreed</i>
<i>upon price</i>

29:21.092 --> 29:23.627
for aiding in its
return to Roman hands.

29:25.262 --> 29:28.098
You set bargain with
this fucking shit?

29:28.165 --> 29:29.766
<i>One of gravest cost.</i>

29:29.834 --> 29:33.370
Coin to set Midas to envy
is carried to your ships.

29:33.437 --> 29:35.605
<i>See yourself</i>
<i>far from my presence.</i>

29:35.673 --> 29:37.540
Or witness rise of morning
sun from the shores

29:37.608 --> 29:39.008
of the afterlife.

29:39.076 --> 29:42.245
<i>I will take most welcomed</i>
<i>leave by</i> <i>night's end.</i>

29:42.313 --> 29:51.888
With all that I have
been promised.

29:51.956 --> 29:53.056
I am a Roman.

29:53.124 --> 29:55.326
One that gave
aid to our enemy,

29:55.393 --> 29:56.527
<i>for</i> <i>whatever the reason.</i>

29:56.594 --> 29:58.262
You cannot do this.

30:00.499 --> 30:02.566
It is already done.

30:02.634 --> 30:04.201
[ whimpering ]

30:12.077 --> 30:13.878
It is the rarest of things,
to see a man

30:13.945 --> 30:15.412
that honors his words.

30:15.480 --> 30:18.048
Stay beyond agreed upon hour,

30:18.116 --> 30:20.651
and you shall know
the bitter truth of it.

30:20.719 --> 30:23.721
May the gods grant
all that you deserve.

30:23.789 --> 30:25.123
<i>mighty Crassus.</i>

30:25.191 --> 30:30.161
As they
have granted Heracleo.

30:30.229 --> 30:32.197
[ whimpering ]

30:37.737 --> 30:40.539
Come, my love.

30:40.607 --> 30:43.008
<i>There are many</i>
<i>wonders beyond these walls</i>

30:43.076 --> 30:58.591
<i>I long</i>
<i>for you to see.</i>

31:09.303 --> 31:12.572
You wish to break words?

31:12.640 --> 31:15.008
Tiberius.

31:15.076 --> 31:16.376
It warms heart,

31:16.444 --> 31:19.346
to see you recovered from
your recent misfortunes.

31:19.414 --> 31:20.948
Come, drink wine,
let us regail --

31:21.015 --> 31:22.983
My time is of short offering.

31:23.051 --> 31:28.755
I am taken with preparing
celebration in your honor.

31:28.823 --> 31:32.626
Gratitude for the effort.

31:32.693 --> 31:34.662
Is there anything
you desire towards it?

31:34.729 --> 31:35.663
Honeyed wine?

31:35.730 --> 31:37.164
Roasted boar?

31:37.232 --> 31:39.834
Oysters plucked from
Poseidon's garden?

31:39.901 --> 31:42.370
[ chuckles ]

31:42.438 --> 31:44.939
I would merely attempt
to honor you with gift.

31:45.007 --> 31:46.174
As you honor me.

31:48.511 --> 31:50.779
This is Canthara.

31:50.847 --> 31:52.380
Born east of the Nile,

31:52.448 --> 31:54.550
but do not judge her for it...

31:54.617 --> 31:56.485
<i>Followers are not</i>
<i>allowed within city walls.</i>

31:56.553 --> 31:58.554
It is a gift from your father.

31:58.621 --> 32:01.456
One I would share.

32:01.524 --> 32:03.658
Did he command
you to do this?

32:03.726 --> 32:07.862
As he commanded
me to pay tribute to you?

32:07.930 --> 32:16.239
Return to more willing flesh.

32:16.306 --> 32:19.176
The boy favors
contention over cunt.

32:22.781 --> 32:25.216
I but favor truth.

32:25.284 --> 32:28.319
The Imperator would
see us to common ground.

32:28.387 --> 32:30.321
I find us far removed.

32:30.389 --> 32:32.224
<i>[ chuckles ]</i>

32:32.291 --> 32:36.194
As mortal from a god.

32:36.262 --> 32:40.198
One set upon a small
band of rebels

32:40.266 --> 32:44.069
with support of a century,

32:44.136 --> 32:47.272
lost his sword,
turned heel and fled.

32:47.340 --> 32:48.440
While the other,

32:48.508 --> 32:51.577
strolled into the jaws
of the beast.

32:51.645 --> 32:54.046
<i>absent weapon,</i>
<i>and</i> <i>brought down</i>

32:54.114 --> 32:56.549
an entire city with
but cunning and silver tongue.

32:56.616 --> 32:58.617
Refresh mind.

32:58.685 --> 33:00.486
Which do you stand?

33:02.922 --> 33:06.925
Upon a day my title
shall be returned to me.

33:06.993 --> 33:08.027
And place you
beneath heel --

33:08.094 --> 33:10.062
I have delayed you too long

33:10.130 --> 33:13.597
from pressing charge.

33:13.665 --> 33:15.966
And the opportunity it brings,

33:16.034 --> 33:18.135
to earn small sum of respect

33:18.203 --> 33:27.312
from those of us that
stand as soldiers.

33:27.380 --> 33:29.882
Oh, and Tiberius?

33:31.551 --> 33:33.519
Oysters.

33:39.026 --> 33:41.327
The streets stand too swollen.

33:41.395 --> 33:46.599
And rooftops alone will not
carry us free of the city.

33:46.667 --> 33:48.334
Gannicus...

33:48.402 --> 33:50.169
Halt.

33:50.237 --> 33:51.337
Part way.

33:51.405 --> 33:53.006
The traitor yet lives.

33:53.074 --> 33:57.844
I move beneath protection
of your Imperator.

33:57.912 --> 34:01.315
<i>Your ship stands</i>
<i>in opposing</i> <i>direction.</i>

34:01.383 --> 34:03.551
I would present precious bounty

34:03.619 --> 34:05.920
with offering of affection,

34:05.988 --> 34:09.024
before taking
to unforgiving sea.

34:09.091 --> 34:14.295
Let them pass.

34:14.362 --> 34:15.597
[ shrieks ]

34:18.101 --> 34:19.634
[ sobbing ]

34:22.605 --> 34:25.206
You look upon me as a monster.

34:25.274 --> 34:28.243
<i>Yet am I not more</i>
<i>desirable fate?</i>

34:28.310 --> 34:31.947
With husband fallen
to the afterlife,

34:32.014 --> 34:35.951
what life would
you have among the Romans?

34:36.018 --> 34:38.753
You are a woman.

34:38.821 --> 34:41.554
No better
than a slave to them.

34:41.621 --> 34:43.054
[ whimpers ]

34:43.121 --> 34:45.822
I bestow
loftier consideration.

34:48.327 --> 34:50.695
I would never
bargain you off,

34:50.763 --> 34:52.197
as Crassus
has done.

34:52.264 --> 34:55.233
Nor would I lock
you in a cage

34:55.301 --> 34:57.402
and pass you about,

34:57.470 --> 34:59.871
as my men would have me do.

35:01.874 --> 35:03.175
No...

35:03.242 --> 35:05.077
you shall stand beside me,

35:05.145 --> 35:08.280
a queen upon the sea.

35:08.347 --> 35:10.482
My greatest treasure.

35:10.549 --> 35:12.851
And all who cross our path

35:12.918 --> 35:15.386
shall know that you are mine.

35:26.132 --> 35:28.166
Heracleo, no!

35:28.234 --> 35:29.901
No!

35:29.969 --> 35:32.371
Apologies for
the pain I cause, my love.

35:32.439 --> 35:34.305
No, no!

35:34.373 --> 35:37.141
[ screaming ]

35:55.560 --> 35:56.827
[ whimpering ]

36:06.872 --> 36:08.006
[ sobbing ]

36:09.942 --> 36:11.709
That is the worst
if it my love.

36:11.777 --> 36:13.744
I do not believe it so.

36:17.149 --> 36:19.616
It lifts spirits
to see you alive,

36:19.684 --> 36:20.784
my friend.

36:20.851 --> 36:23.020
Many of my brothers
did not fare as well.

36:23.087 --> 36:25.155
An act born of necessity,

36:25.223 --> 36:27.924
and raised with heavy heart.

36:27.992 --> 36:31.527
<i>I much liked King</i>
<i>Spartacus and his</i> companions...

36:31.595 --> 36:33.696
Well, most of them.

36:33.764 --> 36:35.397
<i>Yet I was given a choice</i>

36:35.465 --> 36:38.735
between a wealthy life,
or die a merciless death.

36:38.802 --> 36:40.303
Which to a man of my sort,

36:40.371 --> 36:42.372
is no choice at all.

36:42.440 --> 36:44.608
<i>I know what thoughts</i>
<i>pass through mind.</i>

36:44.676 --> 36:47.744
That we are but
shit-eating Cilicians,

36:47.812 --> 36:52.149
no match for a god
of the arena.

36:52.216 --> 36:55.419
Perhaps this is true,
my friend.

36:55.486 --> 36:57.988
<i>Perhaps my sword will find</i>
<i>your woman's throat,</i>

36:58.056 --> 36:59.523
before I fall.

36:59.591 --> 37:02.659
A thing you must appreciate

37:02.727 --> 37:04.661
in such a delicate situation.

37:07.231 --> 37:10.567
She is not my woman.

37:10.635 --> 37:13.339
[ grunts ]

37:13.407 --> 37:15.241
[ shouting ]

37:17.644 --> 37:19.445
[ grunts ]
[ clanging ]

37:22.916 --> 37:24.984
[ swords clanking ]

37:25.052 --> 37:26.553
[ thud ]

37:38.499 --> 37:39.632
Sibyl!

37:39.700 --> 37:40.667
Huh!

37:40.735 --> 37:42.536
So you do care
for the little one, huh?

37:42.604 --> 37:44.772
But it's a pity now that
you have killed her.

37:44.840 --> 37:47.174
No!
[ whimpers ]

37:47.242 --> 37:48.743
[ clanging ]

37:54.482 --> 37:55.549
[ thud ]

37:58.653 --> 38:00.621
[ panting ]

38:02.990 --> 38:05.125
[ whimpering ]

38:11.564 --> 38:13.265
You are hurt?

38:13.333 --> 38:16.234
We must move quickly
before we are discovered.

38:19.906 --> 38:21.974
What of Laeta?

38:22.041 --> 38:24.076
What of her?

38:24.144 --> 38:27.046
We cannot leave her.

38:27.114 --> 38:28.414
She stands Roman.

38:28.482 --> 38:30.583
<i>She won't be seen</i>
<i>with us.</i>

38:30.651 --> 38:33.153
I stand nothing but a slave.

38:36.257 --> 38:38.625
As you once did.

38:42.432 --> 38:43.801
[ shouting ]

38:50.441 --> 38:52.943
[ screaming ]

39:24.643 --> 39:26.810
[ cheering ]

39:29.948 --> 39:32.984
You are truly gifted
at motivating your men, Crassus.

39:33.051 --> 39:35.486
As all great
leaders must be.

39:35.554 --> 39:38.890
Do not allow the Senate to hear
you describe me as such.

39:38.958 --> 39:42.427
They might well tear
you asunder in like fashion.

39:42.495 --> 39:44.796
Give no worry to such thought.

39:44.864 --> 39:46.231
You shall gain their gratitude

39:46.298 --> 39:48.300
in blow struck against
Spartacus,

39:48.367 --> 39:49.868
and return
of Sinuessa en Valle

39:49.935 --> 39:52.604
to rightful embrace
of its citizens.

39:52.671 --> 39:54.873
[ thud ]

39:54.940 --> 39:56.875
We've just begun!

39:56.942 --> 39:59.344
Apologies,
but I must serve correction.

39:59.411 --> 40:01.145
The citizens of this fair city

40:01.213 --> 40:02.280
were all laid to grass

40:02.347 --> 40:03.948
by rebellion's fury.

40:04.016 --> 40:06.717
Not all.

40:06.785 --> 40:10.121
All of note.

40:10.189 --> 40:11.688
What of the Aedile's wife?

40:11.756 --> 40:19.391
She has left these walls,
never to return.

40:19.458 --> 40:23.227
You would claim entire
fucking city for yourself?

40:23.295 --> 40:26.330
A wise man does
not fight for glory alone.

40:28.467 --> 40:30.167
[ grunting ]

40:31.770 --> 40:33.537
The Senate will
not easily swallow

40:33.605 --> 40:35.505
bitter news of such greed.

40:35.573 --> 40:37.040
Greed is but
a word jealous men

40:37.108 --> 40:38.941
inflict upon the ambitious.

40:39.009 --> 40:40.709
<i>They will be made</i>
<i>to see past it</i>

40:40.777 --> 40:44.378
and oblige us
in the spoils of war.

40:44.446 --> 40:45.579
Us?

40:45.647 --> 40:47.881
[ metal thuds ]

40:47.949 --> 40:51.051
I would share in good fortune,
of course.

40:51.119 --> 40:53.953
<i>Perhaps the villa</i>
<i>you now occupy</i>

40:54.021 --> 40:57.657
<i>and a portion of the taxes</i>
<i>levied upon port?</i>

40:57.724 --> 40:58.958
<i>If the Senate</i>

40:59.025 --> 41:00.192
could be persuaded
that we are

41:00.260 --> 41:02.961
deserving of such
bold claim?

41:07.099 --> 41:08.766
[ thuds ]

41:10.468 --> 41:14.003
We have done the impossible.

41:14.071 --> 41:16.172
Surely we should
be rewarded for it.

41:20.109 --> 41:21.943
[ cheering ]

41:32.018 --> 41:36.454
Let us have final
tribute of blood,

41:36.522 --> 41:38.956
in honor of Gaius Julius Caesar!

41:39.024 --> 41:40.991
<i>Caesar!</i>

41:41.059 --> 41:42.292
<i>Caesar!</i>

41:42.360 --> 41:43.793
<i>Caesar!...</i>

41:47.664 --> 41:50.599
Roman fucking cowards.

41:50.667 --> 41:53.802
Shit running your
leg in thought of giving sword

41:53.870 --> 41:55.070
and proper contest.

41:55.138 --> 41:56.671
[ laughter ]

42:00.142 --> 42:01.242
And what would
you do if graced

42:01.310 --> 42:04.179
with such opportunity,
savage?

42:07.050 --> 42:09.351
Such spectacle
is deeply appreciated.

42:09.419 --> 42:12.320
Yet the fall
of Spartacus greeted more so.

42:14.190 --> 42:15.690
[ cheering ]

42:17.727 --> 42:20.262
Carnificina comes to an end.

42:20.330 --> 42:22.698
The rebel king to soon follow.

42:22.765 --> 42:24.266
<i>Imperator.</i>

42:24.334 --> 42:26.802
Honored guests.

42:26.870 --> 42:29.004
We come this day
to praise a man

42:29.072 --> 42:31.874
<i>considered above all others.</i>

42:31.941 --> 42:34.877
A man possessed
of such good fortune

42:34.944 --> 42:38.413
that he must indeed be blessed
by the gods themselves.

42:38.481 --> 42:39.848
[ cheering ]

42:43.585 --> 42:47.221
In storied tradition
of Carnificina,

42:47.289 --> 42:55.497
the ultimate kill
signifies pinnacle of victory.

42:55.565 --> 42:57.966
Shall we award Caesar
the privilege

42:58.034 --> 43:01.036
<i>of delivering fated blow,</i>

43:01.103 --> 43:03.572
with sword of steel

43:03.639 --> 43:07.175
in a war he began
with but...

43:07.243 --> 43:09.878
tongue of silver?

43:09.946 --> 43:11.680
[ cheering ]

43:13.716 --> 43:15.016
<i>Caesar!</i>
<i>Caesar!</i>

43:15.084 --> 43:16.317
<i>Caesar!...</i>

43:18.187 --> 43:19.921
[ cheering ]

43:34.169 --> 43:35.937
You choose your
words with care.

43:36.005 --> 43:38.673
As all who must,
in such position.

43:41.944 --> 43:43.878
[ cheering ]

43:49.885 --> 43:54.089
This man shall fall
not in honor of Caesar.

43:54.157 --> 43:59.661
Nor the great
House of Crassus.

43:59.729 --> 44:03.198
He shall fall in honor
of the glory of Rome!

44:03.266 --> 44:04.733
[ cheering ]

44:06.869 --> 44:09.840
<i>Glory of Rome!</i>

44:27.295 --> 44:28.963
<i>Kill him!</i>

44:29.030 --> 44:30.631
Hold!

44:42.678 --> 44:44.845
It is the will of the gods,

44:44.913 --> 44:49.850
<i>that this beast shall see</i>
<i>himself free of shackles.</i>

44:49.918 --> 44:52.320
So that I may prove
myself worthy

44:52.387 --> 44:56.057
of the praise bestowed upon
me by our Imperator...

44:59.795 --> 45:07.769
and his boy.

45:07.837 --> 45:09.804
[ cheering ]

45:11.607 --> 45:12.541
Come then.

45:12.608 --> 45:13.742
Let us see what challenge

45:13.810 --> 45:15.778
your rebellion truly offers.

45:19.616 --> 45:20.983
[ cheering ]

45:21.051 --> 45:22.318
[ swords clanking ]

45:30.060 --> 45:31.361
They hold celebration?

45:31.428 --> 45:33.363
Executions,
for those among you

45:33.430 --> 45:36.432
yet of this world.

45:36.500 --> 45:37.566
I will have blood
in their name,

45:37.634 --> 45:38.901
upon a day.

45:38.968 --> 45:41.904
Stay to the alleys
and lesser streets as I guide.

45:41.972 --> 45:44.039
And perhaps
live to see it so.

45:46.009 --> 45:47.576
[ swords clanking ]

46:20.644 --> 46:22.745
If this man stands for
all of the rebellion,

46:22.812 --> 46:24.814
<i>celebration may</i>
<i>hold premature.</i>

47:04.242 --> 47:06.009
[ shouting ]

47:15.753 --> 47:17.754
Let this man's death serve as

47:17.822 --> 47:20.890
serve as harbinger
for the fate that we

47:20.958 --> 47:24.160
shall inflict upon
Spartacus himself!

47:24.227 --> 47:25.628
[ cheering ]

47:31.501 --> 47:34.303
Well fought, brother.

47:34.371 --> 47:39.242
Swallow cock,
you Roman shit.

47:39.309 --> 47:41.778
[ grunts ]

47:56.427 --> 47:59.095
<i>Behold!</i>

47:59.163 --> 48:00.530
Their greatest warriors

48:00.598 --> 48:04.801
take their own lives
in fear of Caesar!

48:04.869 --> 48:06.336
<i>Caesar!</i>

48:06.404 --> 48:07.771
Caesar!
<i>Caesar!</i>

48:07.838 --> 48:09.572
[ chanting Caesar ]

48:16.247 --> 48:27.224
<i>[ laughter ]</i>

48:27.292 --> 48:28.525
We will not make it.

48:28.593 --> 48:29.760
Can you ride?

48:32.697 --> 48:34.031
I've seen it done.

48:34.099 --> 48:35.766
Stay close.

48:35.834 --> 48:38.335
We will not turn
back for you.

48:58.557 --> 49:00.057
You there.

49:04.096 --> 49:07.164
I thought Heracleo
granted but one woman.

49:11.704 --> 49:13.404
Where did he come
by this one?

49:18.710 --> 49:20.211
Go!

49:20.278 --> 49:21.779
[ clanking ]

49:33.826 --> 49:35.561
[ screaming ]

49:45.104 --> 49:50.676
[ thud ]
[ screams ]

49:50.744 --> 49:51.877
[ grunts ]

49:54.781 --> 49:56.315
Hiyaa!

49:56.383 --> 49:58.050
Sound the alarm,
you worthless shits!

49:58.118 --> 49:59.051
<i>Close gate!</i>

49:59.119 --> 50:02.154
<i>The rebel escapes!</i>
<i>Man the gate!</i>

50:11.798 --> 50:13.465
[ grunting ]

50:17.103 --> 50:19.137
[ horse blusters ]

50:27.982 --> 50:29.982
[ thud ]

50:38.463 --> 50:40.431
[ screams ]

50:52.578 --> 50:54.912
[ horse neighs ]
Whoa!

51:10.800 --> 51:12.301
Hiyaa!

51:12.368 --> 51:14.236
♪

51:18.642 --> 51:21.277
<i>Why do we not move after him?</i>

51:21.344 --> 51:22.812
Must Julius
fucking Caesar risk

51:22.879 --> 51:24.713
life to kill every
last Rebel himself?

51:24.781 --> 51:25.914
To attempt the ridge
at night would

51:25.982 --> 51:27.383
see us to disadvantage.

51:27.450 --> 51:29.985
And by morning
he will be to the wind

51:30.053 --> 51:31.420
with Spartacus
and the rest

51:31.488 --> 51:33.589
of his rebel horde
you allowed to escape.

51:33.657 --> 51:34.590
I have allowed nothing

51:34.658 --> 51:36.459
but the illusion of hope.

51:36.526 --> 51:37.460
<i>When sun breaks</i>

51:37.527 --> 51:39.462
my legions shall
begin final march,

51:39.529 --> 51:42.065
spurred by dread
of decimation

51:42.132 --> 51:43.232
and dreams of glory sparked

51:43.300 --> 51:45.635
by celebration in your honor.

51:45.703 --> 51:47.903
Spartacus is no fool.

51:47.971 --> 51:50.439
You expect him to wait
in driven snow,

51:50.507 --> 51:54.477
for you to arrive
and announce his end?

51:54.545 --> 51:58.281
That is exactly what I expect.

52:18.903 --> 52:20.103
We cannot remain here.

52:20.171 --> 52:21.738
What would you have us do?

52:21.805 --> 52:23.272
Sprout wings
and soar towards warming

52:23.340 --> 52:24.507
embrace of fucking Apollo?

52:24.575 --> 52:27.643
We should turn
and retake Sinuessa.

52:27.711 --> 52:29.412
The city is lost.

52:29.480 --> 52:30.513
<i>As we shall be,</i>

52:30.581 --> 52:32.148
if we do not act.

52:36.087 --> 52:37.754
Fuck the gods.

53:10.687 --> 53:13.189
And I believed myself
a difficult man to kill.

53:13.256 --> 53:15.023
[ laughing ]

53:23.464 --> 53:25.131
<i>Spartacus!</i>

53:37.579 --> 53:39.947
You bring us a prisoner.

53:40.015 --> 53:41.983
Laeta now stands as you or I,

53:42.050 --> 53:44.385
beneath heel of Republic.

53:44.453 --> 53:45.753
<i>She may yet live,</i>

53:45.821 --> 53:47.555
if her wounds are tended.

53:47.623 --> 53:48.990
See it done.

53:49.057 --> 53:52.026
Lugo.

53:52.094 --> 53:53.795
It is miracle any
of us before you

53:53.863 --> 53:55.196
yet draw breath.

53:57.400 --> 53:58.833
The gods themselves
must have taken

53:58.901 --> 54:00.735
note of delivered prayer,

54:03.139 --> 54:06.374
in order to see
us from certain end.

54:08.277 --> 54:11.145
I fear they
have but delayed it.

54:24.158 --> 54:26.593
How is such
a thing possible?

54:26.661 --> 54:27.761
Nothing is beyond reach

54:27.828 --> 54:30.397
for the richest man
in the Republic.

54:30.465 --> 54:31.965
Crassus.

54:32.033 --> 54:34.434
♪

54:34.501 --> 54:35.635
<i>It was always his intention,</i>

54:35.702 --> 54:38.671
<i>to trap us upon this ridge.</i>

54:38.739 --> 54:42.976
He will march from the city
with his armies behind us.

54:43.044 --> 54:45.512
And when he comes...

54:45.580 --> 54:49.316
death shall
follow in his wake.

54:51.920 --> 54:54.321
[ thunder cracking ]

